{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"**The fix:** The DSL parser stores prompt values as `file(\"prompts/implement.md\")` — a raw `file(...)` wrapper string. The `handleAPIStepContent` handler was treating this raw string as a direct file path, so `os.ReadFile` would try to open a path like `/project/file(\"prompts/implement.md\")`, which doesn't exist. It silently fell through to return \"no content available\".","timestamp":"2026-03-08T04:07:40.855165585Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-08T04:07:40.855206682Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"I added a `resolveStepContent` helper (matching the existing `resolveContent` in the prompt adapter) that strips the `file(\"...\")` wrapper to extract the actual path before reading. This is applied to both `prompt` and `script` config values.","timestamp":"2026-03-08T04:07:40.855211051Z"}
